postcontent:
FNH SCAR 17 with VLTOR rail, ERGO grip, Geissele Super Scar trigger, and HERA linear compensator.   Linear comp is pinned/welded to 13.5" barrel.  Total barrel length is 16.25".
Magpul AFG and (2) 20 roung FN magazines included.
The gun has approximately 1500 rounds through it.  The factory gas port has been replaced with a HD stainless port matched to the linear comp so as to produce correct, reliable function w/out being over gassed.  As anybody that has a SCAR 17 can attest, the factory (PWS) muzzle brake is a beast and very unpleasant for anybody close to you.  The HERA comp really tames this gun down.  I was worried about recoil increasing with the linear comp.  I was pleasantly surprised when it did not increase.  It actually made the gun more pleasant to shoot.  The recoil impulse feels like it was extended over a slightly longer time than before.  It is much easier to stay on target and overall an awesome weapon.  Just trying to free up funds for night vision.No shipping, transfer at a FFL. Doug Turnbull is an amazing artist, and he has rediscovered the lost process of bone ash color case hardening. In addition, Turnbull has refinished the factory checkered stocks in a hand-rubbed oil finish to match Winchester's classic red shading.

title: For Sale:  German Gewehr 98 Amberg 8mm Mauser
postcontent: All parts are matching, including the cleaning rod and stock. The mechanics are excellent and the bore is very fine. The stock is fine. This rifle has the initials "EWB" (EinwohnerWehrBayarn) burned into the right side of the butt, indicating service with the Freikorps just after the war. The Freikorps were mercenary units in Germany, made up of returning veterans, who fought to put down Communist uprisings. They were officially disbanded in 1920, deemed a violation of the Treaty of Versailles. Original, WWI, German Gewehr 98 manufactured at Amberg Arsenal in 1917. Chambered for the 7.92x57mm cartridge (8mm Mauser), The Gew. 98 was the standard German Infantry Weapon of the First World War. This rifle is in very fine condition with about 95% of its factory blued finish remaining and an arsenal bright bolt. No pitting. It is well marked with acceptance stamps.

title: For Sale:  German Gewehr 98 Amberg 8mm Mauser
postcontent: All parts are matching, including the cleaning rod and stock. The mechanics are excellent and the bore is very fine. The stock is fine. This rifle has the initials "EWB" (EinwohnerWehrBayarn) burned into the right side of the butt, indicating service with the Freikorps just after the war. The Freikorps were mercenary units in Germany, made up of returning veterans, who fought to put down Communist uprisings. They were officially disbanded in 1920, deemed a violation of the Treaty of Versailles. Original, WWI, German Gewehr 98 manufactured at Amberg Arsenal in 1917. Chambered for the 7.92x57mm cartridge (8mm Mauser), The Gew. 98 was the standard German Infantry Weapon of the First World War. This rifle is in very fine condition with about 95% of its factory blued finish remaining and an arsenal bright bolt. No pitting. It is well marked with acceptance stamps
